Las Vegas Fire and Rescue get some help from @mayoroflasvegas to show the importance of firework safety while using safe and sane fireworks.🎆 

They also blew up some watermelons to show just how dangerous illegal fireworks can be. 

You can report illegal fireworks at iSpyFireworks.com.

node.text:
Thanks for your patience during the construction and temporary daytime closures on Casino Center Boulevard between Carson and Ogden avenues to improve pedestrian safety. 
 
The temporary daytime closures are necessary to allow the installation of vehicular crash gates to prevent errant vehicles from entering the Casino Center/Fremont crosswalk during shows and special events. The temporary daytime closures are scheduled to be done this weekend. 
 
The gates are part of our ongoing $5.8 million Downtown Pedestrian Safety Program that also includes enhanced bollard security, streetlights, traffic signals, and pedestrian sidewalk improvements near the intersections of Fremont/Main Street, Fremont/Casino Center, Fremont/First Street, Fremont/Third Street, Fremont/Fourth Street, and First/Stewart Avenue.

node.text:
Low water levels at Lake Mead prompted the federal government to issue a water shortage declaration on the Colorado River, the source of most of our drinking water.💧

Southern Nevada will have to take less water from Lake Mead beginning January 2022.
 
@southernnevadawaterauthority 
has more details about what this means for us. 

Look at our stories to swipe up for more information. 📱
